# Retail Sales Analytics Dashboard (Power BI)

## Overview
This project presents an end-to-end Business Intelligence solution built using Power BI. It analyzes retail sales transaction data to identify trends, product performance, store-level insights, and overall sales behavior to support data-driven decision making.

---

## Key Features
- Cleaned and normalized dataset (3NF)
- Star schema data model in Power BI
- Interactive dashboard with KPIs and slicers
- DAX measures for revenue, quantity, and transactions
- Time-based and categorical analysis

---

## Dataset & Modeling
- Normalized Excel dataset with fact and dimension tables
- Sales Master as the fact table
- Product, Customer, Store, Payment, and Date as dimensions
- One-to-many relationships with single-directional filtering

---

## Key Insights
- A small number of products generate a major share of total revenue
- Sales performance varies across months, indicating seasonal patterns
- Certain store locations consistently outperform others
- Digital payment methods are preferred over cash

---

## Tools Used
- Microsoft Excel
- Power BI Desktop
- DAX

---

## Files
- `shop_data_normalised.xlsx`
- `Retail_Sales_Analytics.pbix`

